sers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Masafumi Takada\n| background = non_performing_personnel\n| native_name = \u9ad8\u7530 \u96c5\u53f2\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1970|8|2}}\n| birth_place = [[Inuyama, Aichi]], Japan\n| genre = [[Video game music]]\n| occupation = Composer\n| instrument = Keyboards\n| years_active = 1996\u2013present\n| label = Sound Prestige\n| associated_acts = Jun Fukuda\n| website = {{URL|http://soundprestige.jp/}}\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Masafumi Takada'''|\u9ad8\u7530 \u96c5\u53f2|Takada Masafumi|born August 2, 1970}} is a Japanese [[video game music]] composer, best known for his work on the soundtracks for ''[[killer7]]'', ''[[God Hand]]'', ''[[No More Heroes (video game)|No More Heroes]]'', and the ''[[Earth Defense Force]]'' and ''[[Danganronpa]]'' franchises. Takada often partners up with guitarist and composer Jun Fukuda, and has worked on multiple projects for [[Goichi Suda]]'s studio [[Grasshopper Manufacture]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Sheffield|first=Brandon|date=June 27, 2008|title=Masafumi Takada: Grasshopper's Musical Craftsman|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/feature/132102/masafumi_takada_grasshoppers_.php|website=Gamasutra|accessdate=July 21, 2019}}</ref> Takada publishes his music through his personal record label, Sound Prestige, which he founded in 2008. He is also a founding member of the video game development studio [[Too Kyo Games]], which was founded in 2017 by former members of [[Spike Chunsoft]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Sato|date=September 11, 2018|title=Too Kyo Games Is Led By Danganronpa Staff And Zero Escape Series Creator|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2018/09/11/too-kyo-games-is-led-by-danganronpa-staff-and-zero-escape-series-creator/|website=Siliconera|accessdate=July 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Ref.\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" | 1