P. |date=2001}}\n* Treasure, Geoffrey. ''The Making of Modern Europe, 1648\u20131780'' (3rd ed. 2003). pp 427\u2013462.\n* {{Cite journal |last=Wheeler |first=Nicholas C. |date=Oct 2011 |title=The Noble Enterprise of State Building Reconsidering the Rise and Fall of the Modem State in Prussia and Poland |journal=Comparative Politics |issue=44#1 |pages=21\u201338}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons}}\n{{Wikivoyage|Prussia}}\n{{Wikisource1911Enc|Prussia}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20030727133244/http://www.preussen.de/en/heute.html Preussen.de] (website of the [[House of Hohenzollern]]).\n* {{in lang|de}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20070609110632/http://www.preussen-chronik.de/_/episoden/002020_jsp.html Preu\u00dfen-Chronik.de]\n* [http://www.rulers.org/prusprov.html Administrators of Prussian provinces]\n* [http://www.hv.spk-berlin.de/english/index.php Prussian Cultural Heritage Foundation website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060613210630/http://bpkgate.picturemaxx.com/index.php?LANGUAGE=english Stiftung Preu\u00dfischer Kulturbesitz] (picture archive).\n* [http://www.spsg.de Foundation for Prussian Palaces and Gardens Berlin-Brandenburg]\n* {{in lang|de}} [http://www.lwl.org/westfaelische-geschichte/portal/Internet/ku.php?tab=que&ID=830 Constitutional deed for the Prussian state (\"Imposed Constitution\" \u2013 December 5, 1848)] (full text).\n* {{in lang|de}} [http://www.lwl.org/westfaelische-geschichte/portal/Internet/ku.php?tab=que&ID=831 Constitutional deed for the Prussian state (\"Revised Constitution\" \u2013 January 31, 1850)] (full text).\n* [http://www.gemeindeverzeichnis.de/gem1900//gem1900.htm?preussen1900.htm Administrative Subdivision of the Kingdom of Prussia, 1900/10]\n\n{{Navboxes\n|list =\n{{Territories and provinces of Prussia}}\n{{States of the German Confederation}}\n{{States of the North German Confederation}}\n{{States of the German Empire}}\n{{States of the Weimar Republic}}\n}}\n{{coord missing|Europe}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\